    assessmentFindings: ["Low CO: tachycardia (compensatory), hypotension, cool/mottled extremities, altered sensorium, oliguria","High preload (volume overload): JVD, crackles, S3 gallop, peripheral edema, elevated BNP","Low preload (hypovolemia): flat neck veins, tachycardia, orthostatic hypotension, dry mucous membranes","High afterload: hypertension, loud A2, LV hypertrophy on ECG, increased SVR","Reduced contractility: S3 gallop, displaced PMI, low EF on echo, elevated filling pressures"],
